D'ALENE, Idaho (AP) --One of two men convicted of assaulting a woman and her son outside the headquarters of the Aryan Nations denied being a member of the white supremacist group during testimony in a civil rights case filed against them, the Aryan Nations and the group's founder, Richard Butler.
The Southern Poverty Law Center, which was founded in the 1970s to battle racial bias, won major legal fights against the Ku Klux Klan and other white supremacist groups.
